From: Kamil Lulko <limakzagan@gmail.com>
Subject: ntdll: spoof AMD64 in SystemCpuInformation for wow64 callers on ARM64

After patch 0010 makes SystemSupportedProcessorArchitectures report
AMD64 as the native machine, wine's existing ARM64→AMD64 fallback in
dlls/kernelbase/memory.c:218 (GetNativeSystemInfo) silently breaks.
That fallback was gated on `native_machine != AMD64` — with our spoof,
native_machine IS AMD64, so the fallback skips and the caller falls
through to RtlGetNativeSystemInformation(SystemCpuInformation), which
reads the real ProcessorArchitecture=ARM64 from get_cpuinfo().

For TH-U 1.4.30's Inno Setup 6.4.2 outer .tmp (32-bit / wow64), this
results in "this program can only be installed on versions of Windows
designed for the following processor architectures: x64".

Fix: spoof SystemCpuInformation ProcessorArchitecture to AMD64 on
__aarch64__ — but ONLY for 32-bit wow64 callers (pre-WoA installers
are always 32-bit). 64-bit ARM64EC PE callers (JUCE-based plugins like
TH-U-64) read ProcessorArchitecture to choose their rendering backend;
lying to them makes JUCE pick D3D11 desktop paths that aren't fully
working in our environment and leaves them stuck in a no-render
WM_USER+123 storm.

diff --git a/dlls/ntdll/unix/system.c b/dlls/ntdll/unix/system.c
--- a/dlls/ntdll/unix/system.c
+++ b/dlls/ntdll/unix/system.c
@@ -3009,6 +3009,26 @@ NTSTATUS WINAPI NtQuerySystemInformation( SYSTEM_INFORMATION_CLASS class,
         if (size >= (len = sizeof(SYSTEM_CPU_INFORMATION)))
         {
             SYSTEM_CPU_INFORMATION cpu = get_cpuinfo();
+#ifdef __aarch64__
+            /* fex-pivot: pair with patch 0010 (AMD64-as-native via
+             * SystemSupportedProcessorArchitectures). Wine's existing
+             * ARM64→AMD64 fallback in dlls/kernelbase/memory.c:218
+             * (GetNativeSystemInfo) was gated on
+             * native_machine != AMD64. After patch 0010 native IS AMD64,
+             * so the fallback skips and the i386 wow64 caller (TH-U
+             * 1.4.30 Inno Setup outer .tmp) receives the real
+             * SystemCpuInformation ProcessorArchitecture=ARM64,
+             * triggering "this program can only be installed on x64".
+             *
+             * Spoof ONLY for 32-bit wow64 callers — pre-WoA installers
+             * are always 32-bit. 64-bit ARM64EC PE callers (JUCE plugins
+             * like TH-U-64) read ProcessorArchitecture to choose their
+             * rendering backend; lying to them makes JUCE pick D3D11
+             * desktop paths that aren't fully working in our environment
+             * and leaves them stuck in a no-render WM_USER+123 storm. */
+            if (is_wow64())
+                cpu.ProcessorArchitecture = PROCESSOR_ARCHITECTURE_AMD64;
+#endif
             memcpy( info, &cpu, len );
         }
         else ret = STATUS_INFO_LENGTH_MISMATCH;
